Reasoning: The paper deals with the transmission of short data packets over channels with states, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The use of channel estimation and mismatched decoding also falls under the category of system theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic related to networked information systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper provides bounds on the block error probability, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
